The paper analyzes the degree of collaboration among scientists from different disciplines, which suggests a focus on interdisciplinary research. The methodology is based on bibliometric analysis of publication coauthors, indicating a focus on data analysis and information retrieval (cs.DL, cs.IR). The paper also examines research fields grouped in 9 disciplines, suggesting a focus on interdisciplinary collaboration across different fields (cs.SI, cs.CY). Finally, the paper is published in a journal that focuses on research policy and management strategies, indicating a potential focus on the impact of interdisciplinary collaboration on research management (cs.CR).
